bush singlet
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number: 2
Definition:a black, working singlet; a thick, black, woollen, sleeveless singlet worn by bushmen and other manual workers (because it soaks up sweat without chilling the wearer, and does not show sweatstain and other grime).
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: bushman's singlet
Pronunciation:
Notes: c. 1910 p.c. W.H.B.Orsman (Marlborough).  As long as I can remember and certainly before the First World War, black woollen singlets were always called, and sold in stores as, 'bush singlets'.
